      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\docs\\finops.html</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n570:       </p>\n571: \n572:       <h3>Known providers</h3>\n573:       <table class=\"provider-table\">\n574:         <thead>\n575:           <tr>\n576:             <th>Provider ID</th>\n577:             <th>Type</th>\n578:             <th>Approx. Cost per Call</th>\n579:             <th>Notes</th>\n580:           </tr>\n581:         </thead>\n582:         <tbody>\n583:           <tr>\n584:             <td><code>foundry-local</code></td>\n585:             <td>Local (on-device)</td>\n586:             <td class=\"cost-free\">£0.00 - free</td>\n587:             <td>Microsoft Foundry Local; runs ONNX models on-device. No internet required.</td>\n588:           </tr>\n589:           <tr>\n590:             <td><code>onnx-webnn</code></td>\n591:             <td>Browser (WebNN/WebGPU)</td>\n592:             <td class=\"cost-free\">£0.00 - free</td>\n593:             <td>Runs quantised models in-browser via WebNN. Ideal for air-gapped classrooms.</td>\n594:           </tr>\n595:           <tr>\n596:             <td><code>groq</code></td>\n597:             <td>Cloud API</td>\n598:             <td class=\"cost-cheap\">~£0.0001 per call</td>\n599:             <td>Groq LPU inference; very fast, very cheap. Llama 3, Mixtral.</td>\n600:           </tr>\n601:           <tr>\n602:             <td><code>cerebras</code></td>\n603:             <td>Cloud API</td>\n604:             <td class=\"cost-cheap\">~£0.0001 per call</td>\n605:             <td>Cerebras Wafer-Scale inference; comparable cost to Groq.</td>\n606:           </tr>\n607:           <tr>\n608:             <td><code>openai</code></td>\n609:             <td>Cloud API</td>\n610:             <td class=\"cost-high\">~£0.002+ per call</td>\n611:             <td>OpenAI GPT-4o and family. Blocked by default in educational configurations.</td>\n612:           </tr>\n613:           <tr>\n614:             <td><code>anthropic</code></td>\n615:             <td>Cloud API</td>\n616:             <td class=\"cost-high\">~£0.003+ per call</td>\n617:             <td>Anthropic Claude. Blocked by default in educational configurations.</td>\n618:           </tr>\n619:           <tr>\n620:             <td><code>azure-openai</code></td>\n621:             <td>Cloud API</td>\n622:             <td class=\"cost-high\">~£0.002+ per call</td>\n623:             <td>Azure-hosted OpenAI. Blocked by default in educational configurations.</td>\n624:           </tr>\n625:         </tbody>\n626:       </table>\n627: \n628:       <h3>Routing preference</h3>\n629:       <p>The <code>inference.prefer</code> field controls how the proxy selects a provider:</p>\n630:       <ul>\n631:         <li><strong><code>local</code></strong> - Always use the first available local provider (<code>foundry-local</code>, then <code>onnx-webnn</code>). Fall back to cloud only if no local provider is available and a cloud provider is in <code>allowed_providers</code>.</li>\n632:         <li><strong><code>cloud</code></strong> - Prefer cloud providers. Use local as fallback.</li>\n633:         <li><strong><code>auto</code></strong> - Let the proxy decide based on model requirements and current budget.</li>\n634:       </ul>\n635: \n636:       <div class=\"code-block\" style=\"background: #1a1a2e;\">\n637:         <div class=\"code-block-header\"><span class=\"code-block-lang\">forge · local-only (WJEC / air-gapped)</span><button class=\"copy-btn\">⧉ Copy</button></div>\n638:         <pre style=\"margin:0; font-family: monospace; font-size: 13px; color: #c9d1d9;\">\n639: inference:\n640:   prefer: local\n641:   allowed_providers:\n642:     - foundry-local\n643:     - onnx-webnn\n644:   blocked_providers:\n645:     - openai\n646:     - anthropic\n647:     - azure-openai\n648:     - groq\n649:     - cerebras</pre>\n650:       </div>\n651: \n652:       <div class=\"code-block\" style=\"background: #1a1a2e;\">\n653:         <div class=\"code-block-header\"><span class=\"code-block-lang\">forge · cost-efficient cloud (AWS re/Start)</span><button class=\"copy-btn\">⧉ Copy</button></div>\n654:         <pre style=\"margin:0; font-family: monospace; font-size: 13px; color: #c9d1d9;\">\n655: inference:\n656:   prefer: cloud\n657:   allowed_providers:\n658:     - groq\n659:     - cerebras\n660:     - foundry-local\n661:   blocked_providers:\n662:     - openai\n663:     - azure-openai</pre>\n664:       </div>\n665:     </section>\n666: \n667:     <!-- Alerts and Kill Switch -->\n668:     <section class=\"content-section\">\n669:       <h2 id=\"alerts\">Alerts &amp; Kill Switch</h2>\n670:       <p>\n671:         The <code>finops.alerts</code> section configures spend thresholds that trigger notifications\n672:         and - critically - the <strong>Kill Switch</strong> that halts all further inference when the budget is exhausted.\n673:       </p>\n674: \n675:       <table class=\"spec-table\">\n676:         <thead><tr><th>Property</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>\n677:         <tbody>\n678:           <tr>\n679:             <td><code>warn_at</code></td>\n\n(Showing lines 570-679 of 820. Use offset=680 to continue.)\n</content>",
