      "code": "{\"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\\\sdk\\\\README.md\"}",
      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\sdk\\README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # LAMPForge SDK Core\n2: \n3: The official \"Engine\" of the LAMPForge PDE, providing sovereign AI orchestration, semantic load balancing, and deterministic blueprint generation.\n4: \n5: ## Features\n6: \n7: - **Multi-Tier AI Cascade**: Intelligent routing across Browser-Native (window.ai), Hardware-Accelerated (WebNN/ONNX), Local Servers (Foundry/Ollama), and Cloud Providers (Groq/Cerebras).\n8: - **FinOps & Guardrails**: Sovereign cost control and semantic complexity analysis to prevent resource waste.\n9: - **Protocol-Native**: Built to parse and execute the `.forge` Visual Grammar and Cognitive Taxonomy.\n10: - **Observability**: Integrated line-level telemetry and system-wide logging.\n11: - **Edge-First**: Prioritizes local compute to ensure data sovereignty and carbon efficiency.\n12: \n13: ## Directory Structure\n14: \n15: - `forge-ai.ts`: The core inference orchestrator and cascade logic.\n16: - `forge-protocol.ts`: Implementation of the SDTP (.forge) specification.\n17: - `forge-finops.ts`: Financial guardrails and semantic load-balancing.\n18: - `forge-onnx.ts`: Browser-side WASM/WebNN inference runtime.\n19: - `forge-config.ts`: Persistent configuration and provider management.\n20: - `forge-logger.ts`: Unified telemetry and logging system.\n21: - `forge-types.ts`: Universal type definitions for blueprints and schemas.\n22: \n23: ## Usage\n24: \n25: ```typescript\n26: import { forgeSchema } from \"@sdk/forge-ai\";\n27: \n28: const { blueprint, provider } = await forgeSchema(\n29:   \"A simple blog with posts\",\n30:   \"competent\"\n31: );\n32: \n33: console.log(`Generated via ${provider}:`, blueprint);\n34: ```\n35: \n36: ## Sovereignty Principle\n37: \n38: This SDK is designed to be **Hyper-Sovereign**. It probes local capabilities (`window.ai`, Local LLMs) before ever making a network request, ensuring that the development process remains private and efficient by default.\n\n(End of file - total 38 lines)\n</content>",
