      "code": "{\"offset\": 750, \"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\\\docs\\\\finops.html\", \"limit\": 70}",
      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\docs\\finops.html</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n750:     </section>\n751: \n752:     <!-- Education -->\n753:     <section class=\"content-section\">\n754:       <h2 id=\"education\">Why This Matters for Education</h2>\n755: \n756:       <h3>First-generation students</h3>\n757:       <p>\n758:         Many students using SDTP are first-generation university or college applicants who cannot\n759:         absorb unexpected AI costs. A misconfigured environment that silently sends requests to OpenAI GPT-4o\n760:         could run up a £20–£50 bill in a single day of coursework. SDTP makes it <em>impossible</em> for\n761:         this to happen by default - the <code>blocked_providers</code> list and zero budget cap are enforced\n762:         at the protocol level, not as an optional best practice.\n763:       </p>\n764: \n765:       <h3>Welsh schools and the Hwb platform</h3>\n766:       <p>\n767:         Welsh secondary schools operating through the Hwb platform typically have per-student IT budgets\n768:         of under £100/year. AI-assisted development tools must be free or near-free to be deployable at scale.\n769:         SDTP's local inference providers (<code>foundry-local</code> via Microsoft's Windows AI platform,\n770:         and <code>onnx-webnn</code> for in-browser inference) provide full AI assistance at <strong>£0.00 per call</strong>,\n771:         running on hardware already present in school computer suites.\n772:       </p>\n773: \n774:       <h3>School IT departments</h3>\n775:       <p>\n776:         School IT departments need <em>auditable</em> records of any cloud spend. The FinOps ledger file\n777:         (<code>state/finops-ledger.json</code>) provides a complete, append-only record of every inference call\n778:         including zero-cost local calls - that can be reviewed by the school's data protection officer\n779:         or IT manager. No cloud credentials are embedded in <code>.forge</code> files; they are stored\n780:         separately in <code>state/credentials.json</code> with restricted file permissions.\n781:       </p>\n782: \n783:       <div class=\"callout callout-info\">\n784:         <span class=\"callout-icon\">ℹ️</span>\n785:         <div>\n786:           <strong>Summary of benefits for Education:</strong>\n787:           <ul>\n788:             <li>Eliminates \"bill shock\" for students and families.</li>\n789:             <li>Enables free AI assistance via local hardware.</li>\n790:             <li>Provides auditable trails for school IT compliance.</li>\n791:             <li>Simplifies budget management for departments.</li>\n792:           </ul>\n793:         </div>\n794:       </div>\n795:     </section>\n796: \n797:     <!-- Navigation -->\n798:     <section class=\"content-section\">\n799:       <div class=\"quick-cards\">\n800:         <a href=\"specification.html\" class=\"quick-card\">\n801:           <div class=\"quick-card-icon\">📋</div>\n802:           <div class=\"quick-card-title\">Specification</div>\n803:           <div class=\"quick-card-desc\">Full protocol reference</div>\n804:         </a>\n805:         <a href=\"examples.html\" class=\"quick-card\">\n806:           <div class=\"quick-card-icon\">📁</div>\n807:           <div class=\"quick-card-title\">Examples</div>\n808:           <div class=\"quick-card-desc\">Real-world .forge files</div>\n809:         </a>\n810:         <a href=\"implementors.html\" class=\"quick-card\">\n811:           <div class=\"quick-card-icon\">🔧</div>\n812:           <div class=\"quick-card-title\">Implementors Guide</div>\n813:           <div class=\"quick-card-desc\">Build a .forge runtime</div>\n814:         </a>\n815:       </div>\n816:     </section>\n817:   </div>\n818: </div>\n819: </body>\n\n(Showing lines 750-819 of 820. Use offset=820 to continue.)\n</content>",
