    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "read",
      "code": "{\"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\\\docs\\\\learning.html\", \"offset\": 100, \"limit\": 60}",
      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\docs\\learning.html</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n100:         <li><strong>Privacy Concerns</strong>: Uploading student code to cloud providers may violate school or local authority data protection policies.</li>\n101:         <li><strong>Assessment Integrity</strong>: Examining bodies (like WJEC) require clear proof that work is the student's own, not generated by an AI.</li>\n102:       </ul>\n103: \n104:       <p>SDTP was built from the ground up to solve these specific problems.</p>\n105:     </section>\n106: \n107:     <!-- Air-Gapped Operation -->\n108:     <section class=\"content-section\">\n109:       <h2 id=\"air-gapped\">Air-Gapped Operation</h2>\n110:       <p>\n111:         The most powerful feature of SDTP in a learning environment is its ability to operate\n112:         entirely without an internet connection.\n113:       </p>\n114: \n115:       <h3>Local Inference (Foundry Local)</h3>\n116:       <p>\n117:         By leveraging Microsoft's <strong>Windows AI</strong> platform, the IDE can run local ONNX models\n118:         directly on the computer's CPU or GPU. This means:\n119:       </p>\n120:       <ul>\n121:         <li>No student data ever leaves the local network.</li>\n122:         <li>Zero latency: responses are near-instant.</li>\n123:         <li>Zero cost: no API bills for the school.</li>\n124:       </ul>\n125: \n126:       <div class=\"code-block\">\n127:         <div class=\"code-block-header\"><span class=\"code-block-lang\">forge · offline-first configuration</span><button class=\"copy-btn\">⧉ Copy</button></div>\n128:         <pre><code>finops:\n129:   inference:\n130:     prefer: local\n131:     allowed_providers: [foundry-local, onnx-webnn]\n132:     blocked_providers: [openai, anthropic]</code></pre>\n133:       </div>\n134:     </section>\n135: \n136:     <!-- The Learning Supervisor -->\n137:     <section class=\"content-section\">\n138:       <h2 id=\"supervisor\">The Learning Supervisor</h2>\n139:       <p>\n140:         In a standard development team, a \"Supervisor\" might automate deployments.\n141:         In SDTP, the Supervisor acts as a <strong>Pedagogical Bridge</strong>.\n142:       </p>\n143: \n144:       <table class=\"spec-table\">\n145:         <thead><tr><th>Supervisor Task</th><th>Impact on Learning</th></tr></thead>\n146:         <tbody>\n147:           <tr>\n148:             <td><code>scaffold_level</code></td>\n149:             <td>Adjusts how much \"help\" the AI gives based on student progress.</td>\n150:           </tr>\n151:           <tr>\n152:             <td><code>curriculum_alignment</code></td>\n153:             <td>Ensures the AI uses terminology and patterns from the WJEC specification.</td>\n154:           </tr>\n155:           <tr>\n156:             <td><code>explainer_mode</code></td>\n157:             <td>The AI must explain *why* it is suggesting a change before applying it.</td>\n158:           </tr>\n159:         </tbody>\n\n(Showing lines 100-159 of 202. Use offset=160 to continue.)\n</content>",
