      "code": "{\"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\\\RandD\\\\finops_explainer_and_rationale.md\", \"offset\": 170, \"limit\": 80}",
      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\RandD\\finops_explainer_and_rationale.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n170: ## The .forge FinOps Architecture\n171: \n172: ### Configuration Schema\n173: \n174: ```yaml\n175: finops:\n176:   budget:\n177:     max_monthly_cloud: 0.00      # £0 by default - SAFE\n178:     max_inference_calls: 50      # Hard limit per session\n179:     currency: GBP                # Local currency\n180: \n181:   inference:\n182:     prefer: local                # On-device first\n183:     allowed_providers:\n184:      - foundry-local            # Microsoft Foundry (free, local)\n185:      - onnx-webnn               # Browser-native (free)\n186:      - ollama-local             # Self-hosted (free)\n187:     blocked_providers:\n188:      - openai                   # Explicitly blocked\n189:      - anthropic                # Explicitly blocked\n190:      - azure-openai             # Explicitly blocked\n191: \n192:   alerts:\n193:     warn_at: 0.80                # 80% of budget → warning\n194:     kill_at: 1.00                # 100% of budget → STOP\n195:     notify:\n196:      - console                  # Show in PDE\n197:      - teacher                  # Alert teacher dashboard\n198: \n199:   accounting:\n200:     log_inference_costs: true    # Every call logged\n201:     session_budget_file: \"state/finops-ledger.json\"\n202: ```\n203: \n204: ### The Inference Cascade with FinOps\n205: \n206: ```mermaid\n207: flowchart TD\n208:     subgraph INTENT[\"Student Intent\"]\n209:         I1[\"Student submits prompt\"]\n210:     end\n211: \n212:     I1 --> CHECK{\"Budget<br/>remaining?\"}\n213: \n214:     CHECK -->|\"NO\"| BLOCKED[\"BLOCKED<br/>Session budget exhausted\"]\n215:     CHECK -->|\"YES\"| CASCADE\n216: \n217:     subgraph CASCADE[\"Inference Cascade\"]\n218:         C1[\"Try: Browser-native<br/>(ONNX/WebNN)\"] -->|\"fail\"| C2[\"Try: Local server<br/>(Foundry/Ollama)\"]\n219:         C2 -->|\"fail\"| C3{\"Cloud<br/>allowed?\"}\n220:         C3 -->|\"NO\"| FALLBACK[\"Use: Offline fallback\"]\n221:         C3 -->|\"YES\"| C4[\"Try: Cloud provider\"]\n222:         C4 --> LOG\n223:     end\n224: \n225:     C1 -->|\"success\"| LOG\n226:     C2 -->|\"success\"| LOG\n227:     FALLBACK --> LOG\n228: \n229:     subgraph ACCOUNTING[\"FinOps Accounting\"]\n230:         LOG[\"Log: provider, tokens, cost\"]\n231:         LOG --> UPDATE[\"Update: session budget\"]\n232:         UPDATE --> LEDGER[\"Write: finops-ledger.json\"]\n233:     end\n234: \n235:     LEDGER --> RESPONSE[\"Return: AI response to student\"]\n236: \n237:     style BLOCKED fill:#ff6b6b,stroke:#c92a2a,color:#fff\n238:     style CASCADE fill:#d0ebff,stroke:#339af0\n239:     style ACCOUNTING fill:#fff3bf,stroke:#fab005\n240: ```\n241: \n242: > **How to read:** Every inference request passes through budget check first. If budget exhausted, request is blocked (red). If budget available, cascade tries providers in order (local first, cloud last). Every call is logged with cost. Budget is updated in real-time.\n243: \n244: ---\n245: \n246: ## Why FinOps Makes SDTP Salient\n247: \n248: ### The Market Context (2026)\n249: \n\n(Showing lines 170-249 of 429. Use offset=250 to continue.)\n</content>",
