      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\.agents\\skills\\edge-ai-inference\\SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: name: edge-ai-inference\n3: description: Specialized skill for managing, benchmarking, and troubleshooting browser-native AI inference.\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Edge AI Inference Skill\n7: \n8: This skill provides the Antigravity agent with specialized procedures for managing the Sovereign Edge AI stack within the LAMPForge platform.\n9: \n10: ## Core Capabilities\n11: \n12: ### 1. Capability Detection\n13: When asked about AI performance or availability, always check:\n14: - **`window.ai`**: Status of Gemini Nano (Prompt API).\n15: - **`navigator.ml` (WebNN)**: Availability of hardware-accelerated neural networks.\n16: - **`navigator.gpu` (WebGPU)**: Status of graphics acceleration for ONNX.\n17: \n18: ### 2. Browser Flag Verification\n19: If inference is failing or slow, guide the user to check:\n20: - `chrome://flags/#optimization-guide-on-device-model` -> Set to **Enabled (Bypass requirement)**.\n21: - `chrome://flags/#prompt-api-for-gemini-nano` -> Set to **Enabled**.\n22: - `chrome://flags/#enable-webnn` -> Set to **Enabled**.\n23: \n24: ### 3. Troubleshooting Matrix\n25: \n26: | Symptom | Cause | Resolution |\n27: | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n28: | `window.ai` is undefined | No experimental flags | Enable Gemini Nano flags in browser |\n29: | Download stuck at 0% | Optimization Guide issues | Trigger `triggerModelDownload` and wait for progress |\n30: | `WebNN` not found | Outdated browser or disabled flag | Check Edge/Chrome version (>129) and enable WebNN flag |\n31: | Memory OOM | Concurrent sessions | Clear internal `forgeLog` and restart session |\n32: \n33: ## Operational Procedures\n34: \n35: ### Running an Inference Benchmark\n36: 1. Navigate to the **Sovereign Catalogue** tab.\n37: 2. Select a model (e.g., *Forge Router Micro*).\n38: 3. Execute the \"Run Benchmark\" probe.\n39: 4. Capture the latency (ms) and tokens/sec for the log.\n40: \n41: ### Verification Commands\n42: If the user has access to a terminal, you can request they check:\n43: ```powershell\n44: # Check for Node-based bridge availability\n45: netstat -ano | findstr :3000\n46: ```\n47: \n48: ## Defensive Moats\n49: Always prioritize local inference to maintain the **Unit Economics Moat** ($0 marginal cost) and the **Data Residency Moat** (No cloud exfiltration).\n\n(End of file - total 49 lines)\n</content>",
