      "type": "answer",
      "text": "Here is the complete report of all findings across the LAMPForge PDE codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. What Is Foundry Local Inference?\n\n**Foundry Local** is Microsoft's local AI inference runtime -- part of the **Windows AI** platform. It runs ONNX models directly on-device (CPU, GPU, or NPU) with zero internet requirement and zero per-call cost. The codebase refers to it as:\n\n- Provider ID: `foundry-local`\n- Display name: **\"Foundry Local\"** (sometimes \"Microsoft Foundry Local\")\n- Cost: **Free (£0.00)**\n- Privacy: no data leaves the machine\n\nFrom `docs/finops.html` (line 584-587):\n> `<code>foundry-local</code>` -- Microsoft Foundry Local; runs ONNX models on-device. No internet required.\n\nFrom `docs/learning.html` (line 115-118):\n> By leveraging Microsoft's **Windows AI** platform, the IDE can run local ONNX models directly on the computer's CPU or GPU.\n\n---\n\n## 2. How Does It Work? -- API Format, Endpoints, Discovery\n\n### 2.1 Endpoint Discovery\n\nFoundry runs as a local HTTP server. The codebase discovers it by probing a set of well-known ports:\n\n**Probable ports** (from `sdk/forge-ai.ts` line 42):\n```\nconst PROBABLE_PORTS = [55335, 5272, 5273, 50674];\n```\n\nAdditional ports probed in the benchmark (`lampforge-benchmark.html` line 1024):\n```\nconst ports = [5272, 55335, 62583];\n```\n\n**Discovery flow** (`sdk/forge-ai.ts`, function `discoverFoundryEndpoint()` lines 47-76):\n1. If `config.foundryPort` is set (from user config), use it directly.\n2. If previously cached, use the cached port.\n3. Otherwise, probe each port by hitting `http://localhost:{port}/openai/status` with a 1.5-second timeout per port.\n4. On success, cache the port and return the full endpoint URL.\n\n### 2.2 API Endpoints\n\n| Endpoint | Purpose | Used In |\n|----------|---------|---------|\n| `http://localhost:{port}/v1/chat/completions` | Primary: Chat completions (text generation) | `discoverFoundryEndpoint()`, `tryFoundryLocal()`, `tryArchRouter()` |\n| `http://localhost:{port}/v1/models` | List available models | `discoverFoundryModel()`, `probeFoundryModels()` in `edge-ai.ts`, benchmark |\n| `http://localhost:{port}/openai/status` | Health-check/probe for discovery | `discoverFoundryEndpoint()` |\n| `http://localhost:{port}/v1/chat/completions` (with tools) | Tool-calling mode | `tryFoundryLocal()` Strategy 1 |\n\nAll endpoints use the standard REST conventions and the OpenAI-compatible chat completions format.\n\n### 2.3 Chat Completions Payload (OpenAI-compatible)\n\nThe codebase sends requests with this structure (from `tryFoundryLocal` and `tryArchRouter`):\n\n**Tool-calling payload** (Strategy 1, `forge-ai.ts` lines 497-507):\n```json\n{\n  \"model\": \"qwen2.5-0.5b\",\n  \"messages\": [\n    { \"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"...\" },\n    { \"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"User intent here\" }\n  ],\n  \"tools\": [{\n    \"type\": \"function\",\n    \"function\": {\n      \"name\": \"generate_blueprint\",\n      \"parameters\": { ... }\n    }\n  }],\n  \"tool_choice\": { \"type\": \"function\", \"function\": { \"name\": \"generate_blueprint\" } },\n  \"temperature\": 0.2,\n  \"max_tokens\": 4096\n}\n```\n\n**JSON-in-prompt fallback payload** (Strategy 2, `forge-ai.ts` lines 510-521):\n```json\n{\n  \"model\": \"qwen2.5-0.5b\",\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"...\\n\\nIMPORTANT: Since tool-calling is not available, respond with a raw JSON object...\"\n    },\n    { \"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"User intent here\" }\n  ],\n  \"temperature\": 0.2,\n  \"max_tokens\": 4096\n}\n```\n\n**Route classification payload** (Arch-Router, `forge-ai.ts` lines 413-424):\n```json\n{\n  \"model\": \"qwen2.5-1.5b-instruct-generic-cpu:4\",\n  \"messages\": [\n    { \"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful assistant designed to find the best suited route...\" },\n    { \"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Given the following route policies:\\n- ...\\n\\nClassify...\" }\n  ],\n  \"temperature\": 0,\n  \"max_tokens\": 50\n}\n```\n\n### 2.4 Models returned by `/v1/models`\n\nThe endpoint returns OpenAI-compatible JSON:\n```json\n{\n  \"data\": [\n    { \"id\": \"phi-3.5-mini\" },\n    { \"id\": \"qwen2.5-0.5b\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nThe codebase accesses `data[0].id` (from `discoverFoundryModel()`) or iterates `data.data` / `data.models` (from `probeFoundryModels()` in `edge-ai.ts`).\n\n---\n\n## 3. What Models Does It Support?\n\n### 3.1 Model Alias Used in Code\n\nThe primary model alias used when calling Foundry is:\n\n```typescript\nconst modelAlias = \"qwen2.5-0.5b\";   // forge-ai.ts line 493\n```\n\nThe Arch-Router uses a different model:\n```typescript\nmodel: \"qwen2.5-1.5b-instruct-generic-cpu:4\"   // forge-ai.ts line 414\n```\n\n### 3.2 Sovereign Model Registry\n\nFrom `src/lib/model-registry.ts` -- the model card for Foundry:\n\n```typescript\n{\n  id: \"forge-architect\",\n  name: \"Forge Architect Pro\",\n  family: \"Llama 3\",\n  parameters: \"8B\",\n  format: \"GGUF\",\n  providerType: \"foundry-local\",\n  capabilities: [\"complex-reasoning\", \"multi-file-editing\", \"architecture\"],\n  description: \"Heavy-duty local model requiring the Foundry node. Best for whole-file rewrites and large context windows.\",\n  sdtpRole: \"Deep Tech Code Generation\",\n  status: \"available-now\",\n  downloadSize: \"4.7GB\",\n  accuracyRef: \"Llama 3 base accuracy\"\n}\n```\n\n### 3.3 Known / Discovered Models\n\nFrom the ledger examples in `spec/FINOPS.md` line 288:\n```\n\"model\":\"phi-3.5-mini\"\n```\n\nFrom the `probeFoundryModels` function in `edge-ai.ts`, the models are whatever the Foundry server returns via `/v1/models`. Each is tagged with:\n```typescript\nprovider: \"foundry-local\",\ncapabilities: [\"text-generation\", \"onnx\"]\n```\n\n### 3.4 Inferred Model Support\n\nModels likely run through Foundry, based on references throughout the codebase:\n- **Qwen2.5 0.5B** (int4 ONNX) -- for blueprint generation and routing\n- **Qwen2.5 1.5B** (CPU-optimized) -- for Arch-Router intent classification\n- **Phi-3.5-mini / Phi-4-mini** -- for general reasoning\n- **Llama 3 8B** (GGUF) -- for the \"Forge Architect Pro\" heavy-duty model\n- Any ONNX model the server exposes via `/v1/models`\n\n---\n\n## 4. How Does the Codebase Interact with Foundry? -- The Full Inference Cascade\n\n### 4.1 The 4-Stage Inference Cascade\n\nThe core orchestrator is `sdk/forge-ai.ts`, function `forgeSchema()` (line 834). It implements a multi-tier fallback chain:\n\n```\nStage 1: Route Classification\n   ├── tryOnnxRouter()      -- ONNX Runtime Web (browser-native, 8s timeout)\n   └── tryArchRouter()      -- Foundry Local (if ONNX failed)\n         Calls Foundry at /v1/chat/completions with model \"qwen2.5-1.5b-instruct-generic-cpu:4\"\n\nStage 1.5: Browser-Native LLM\n   └── tryBrowserAI()       -- window.ai (Gemini Nano / Prompt API)\n\nStage 2: Blueprint Generation (ONNX)\n   └── tryOnnxFallback()    -- ONNX Runtime Web (WebNN/WebGPU/WASM, 30s timeout)\n\nStage 3: Local Server Generation\n   ├── tryFoundryLocal()    -- Foundry Local (2 strategies: tool-calling, then JSON fallback)\n   └── (Ollama placeholder) -- Not yet implemented\n\nStage 4: Cloud Fallbacks\n   ├── tryGroq()            -- Groq Cloud API\n   └── tryCerebras()        -- Cerebras Cloud API\n```\n\n### 4.2 The Ordering is Dynamic\n\nThe cascade respects FinOps semantic routing:\n- If `dynamicPrefer === \"cloud\"` -- try cloud first, then local\n- If `dynamicPrefer === \"local\"` or `\"auto\"` (default) -- try local first, then cloud\n\nThe semantic router (`SemanticEmbedder`) modifies the preference based on intent complexity score and battery level.\n\n### 4.3 Foundry's Role in the Cascade\n\n**As Arch-Router (Stage 1 fallback):**\nWhen the ONNX browser router fails, `tryArchRouter()` (line 393) discovers the Foundry endpoint and sends a classification request. If Foundry is not available, it falls through to a default route.\n\n**As Blueprint Generator (Stage 3 primary):**\n`tryFoundryLocal()` (line 473) is the central generation function. It:\n1. Discovers the Foundry endpoint (cache-aware)\n2. Attempts **Strategy 1: Tool-calling** -- sends a request with `tools` and `tool_choice` parameters to get structured JSON output\n3. If tool-calling fails or returns no blueprint, attempts **Strategy 2: JSON-in-prompt** -- sends a raw JSON request in the system prompt\n4. Each strategy has a 120-second timeout\n5. On success, validates the blueprint using `validateBlueprint()` and returns it\n\n### 4.4 Configuration\n\nFrom `sdk/forge-config.ts`, the Foundry port can be manually configured:\n```typescript\nexport interface ForgeAIConfig {\n    foundryPort: number | null;   // default: null (auto-discovery)\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\nFrom `.forge` files, Foundry is configured via FinOps:\n```yaml\nfinops:\n  inference:\n    prefer: local\n    allowed_providers:\n      - foundry-local      # <-- enabled\n      - onnx-webnn\n    blocked_providers:\n      - openai\n      - anthropic\n```\n\n### 4.5 Capability Detection in `edge-ai.ts`\n\nThe function `probeFoundryModels()` (line 98) probes ports 5273 and 5272 (3-second timeout each) at `/v1/models`. If models are found, the capability `foundryLocal: true` is set and the tier becomes `\"foundry-local\"`.\n\n### 4.6 Provider Health Checks\n\n`checkAllProviders()` (line 103) probes Foundry endpoint and model, showing \"online\" or \"offline\" status in the admin panel. The self-heal mechanism `runSelfHeal()` (line 827) resets the cached port and re-discovers.\n\n### 4.7 CO2 Estimation\n\nIn `edge-ai.ts`, Foundry-local inference is estimated at **~0.1g CO2** per call (99% reduction vs cloud).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Key Files Containing Foundry/Local-Inference/ONNX/WebNN/WASM Code\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\sdk\\forge-ai.ts` | Core inference orchestrator, Foundry endpoint discovery, Arch-Router, Foundry Local blueprint generation, Groq/Cerebras cloud fallbacks, self-heal |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\sdk\\forge-onnx.ts` | ONNX Runtime Web engine, WebGPU/WebNN/WASM providers, Pavone state persistence, token generation loop |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\sdk\\forge-config.ts` | Config schema including `foundryPort` setting |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\src\\lib\\edge-ai.ts` | Edge AI capability detection, Foundry model probing, CO2 estimation, browser-native inference |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\src\\lib\\model-registry.ts` | Sovereign model catalogue including Foundry model card |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\src\\lib\\browser-flags.ts` | Browser feature detection (WebNN, WebGPU, WASM flags) |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\spec\\FINOPS.md` | FinOps specification: provider cost tables, budget enforcement, Foundry pricing |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\spec\\SPECIFICATION.md` | Protocol spec: `honc` stack includes ONNX, inference cascade requirements |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\docs\\finops.html` | FinOps docs: provider table with `foundry-local`, inference preferences |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\docs\\sovereign-ai-inference.md` | Sovereign inference rationale: ONNX/WebNN, edge-native, inference cascade |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\docs\\ARCHITECTURE.md` | Architecture diagram showing Foundry Local as optional local AI provider |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\sdk\\README.md` | SDK overview mentioning multi-tier AI cascade |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\examples\\air-gapped.forge` | Example .forge file with `foundry-local` in allowed_providers |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\examples\\minimal.forge` | Minimal example |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\docs\\learning.html` | \"Local Inference (Foundry Local)\" documentation section |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\docs\\examples.html` | Example configs with `foundry-local` |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\docs\\specification.html` | Spec HTML showing `foundry-local` in allowed_providers |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\lampforge-benchmark.html` | Benchmark tool: probes Foundry on ports 5272, 55335, 62583 |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\launcher.html` | Startup checker: probes WebNN, WASM, WASM SIMD |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\prebake-models.html` | Pre-bake models: checks WebNN API availability |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\download-onnx.mjs` | Downloads ONNX model from HuggingFace |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\src\\lib\\forge-embedder.ts` | ONNX-based semantic embedder for intent analysis |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\src\\lib\\forge-opfs-cache.ts` | OPFS cache for large ONNX models |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\src\\lib\\forge-cloud-adapter.ts` | Cloud adapter: uploads ONNX models to R2 |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\public\\sw.js` | Service Worker: caches WASM binaries and ONNX models |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\package.json` | Dependencies: `onnxruntime-web: ^1.24.3` |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\RandD\\finops_explainer_and_rationale.md` | FinOps rationale: Foundry in inference cascade diagram |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\RandD\\custom_browser_native_llm_architecture.md` | ONNX architecture deep-dive |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\RandD\\market_intelligence_browser_ai_platform_stability.md` | WASM/WebNN/ONNX stability analysis |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\RandD\\strategic_finops_vision.md` | Strategic vision: Foundry cost model |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\internal\\docs-private\\sovereign_pde_architecture.md` | Deep architecture doc: 4-stage cascade, WebNN routing, Foundry details |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\internal\\docs-private\\green_computing_thought_leadership.md` | Environmental impact of local inference |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\RAEng_Technical_Report_Local_AI_Optimization.md` | RAEng technical report on local AI optimization |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\cli\\commands\\init.mjs` | CLI: air-gapped intent mentions local inference |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\cli\\commands\\examples.mjs` | CLI: air-gapped example description |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\docs\\RATIONALE.md` | WASM/SQLite rationale |\n| `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\LAMPForge_SDTP\\forge-flow-learn-0d5b3821\\.agents\\skills\\edge-ai-inference\\SKILL.md` | Agent skill: troubleshooting Foundry/WebNN |\n\n---\n\n## Summary Answering Your Questions\n\n**1. What is Foundry Local Inference?**\nIt is Microsoft's on-device AI inference runtime that runs ONNX models locally on the student's machine. It provides zero-cost, zero-latency, fully private inference without any internet connection. In the LAMPForge codebase, it is the primary local provider for heavy-lift model inference (blueprint generation and intent routing) after browser-native ONNX falls through.\n\n**2. How does it work?**\nIt runs as a local HTTP server on well-known ports (55335, 5272, 5273, 50674, 62583). The codebase auto-discovers it by probing `http://localhost:{port}/openai/status`, then uses OpenAI-compatible `/v1/chat/completions` and `/v1/models` endpoints. Tool-calling is attempted first (structured JSON via `tools` parameter), with a JSON-in-prompt fallback if tool-calling is unavailable. The endpoint URL format is `http://localhost:{port}/v1/chat/completions`.\n\n**3. What models does it support?**\n- **Qwen2.5 0.5B** (int4 ONNX) -- routing and blueprint generation\n- **Qwen2.5 1.5B** (CPU-optimized) -- Arch-Router classification\n- **Phi-3.5-mini** -- general reasoning\n- **Phi-4-mini** -- general reasoning (mentioned in docs)\n- **Llama 3 8B** (GGUF) -- \"Forge Architect Pro\" for complex tasks\n- Any model the Foundry server exposes via `/v1/models`\n\n**4. How does the codebase interact with it?**\n- **Auto-discovery** at startup by probing well-known ports\n- **Intent routing** via `tryArchRouter()` in `forge-ai.ts`\n- **Blueprint generation** via `tryFoundryLocal()` using two strategies (tool-calling, then JSON fallback)\n- **Capability detection** via `probeFoundryModels()` in `edge-ai.ts`\n- **Health checking** via `checkAllProviders()` and `runSelfHeal()`\n- **Benchmarking** via `lampforge-benchmark.html`\n- **FinOps governance** -- always costs £0.00, recorded in ledger for transparency\n- **CO2 estimation** at ~0.1g per call (99% reduction vs cloud)\n- **Configuration** via `.forge` YAML files and `forge-config.ts`",
